quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  78,31,"On that Day, the righteous will certainly achieve their Heartâ€™s desires"
  78,32,"beautiful gardens, vineyards"
  78,33,and young women of their own age
  78,34,and overflowing cups
  78,35,"they shall hear no vanity, nor any falsehood"
  78,36,a recompense from your Lord and a gift beyond their account
  78,37,"from the Compassionate, Who is the Lord of the heavens, the earth and all that lies between them; before Whom no one shall be able to speak"
  78,38,"On that Day, the Spirit (Gabriel) and the angels shall stand in their ranks; none shall speak except the one to whom the Compassionate (Allah) shall grant permission to speak, and he will speak straight to the point"
  78,39,"That Day is a sure reality. Let him who desires, seek a way back to his Lord"
  78,40,"Indeed We have forewarned you of an imminent punishment which lies close-at-hand, on the Day when man shall see what his hands have sent forth and the unbeliever will cry: \"I wish! I could remain merely dust"
  79,1,By those angels who violently pull out the souls of the wrongdoers
  79,2,and those who gently draw out the souls of the righteous
  79,3,and those who glide about swiftly through space
  79,4,then speed headlong to carry out the commands of Allah
  79,5,and those who regulate the affairs of the world
  79,6,The Day on which the quake shall cause a violent commotion
  79,7,which will be followed by another violent commotion
  79,8,"and on that Day, hearts shall be pounding with terror"
  79,9,and sight shall be downcast
  79,10,"The unbelievers say: \"Shall we really be restored to our former state (life)"
  79,11,when we shall have become hollow bones
  79,12,"They further say: \"It would then be a fruitless restoration"
  79,13,They should know that it shall be only a single shout
  79,14,and they will be back to life in open plain
  79,15,Have you heard the story of Moses